"Arinobu T., Ishiwatari R., Kaiho K., Lamolda M.A., Seno H.","Abrupt and massive influx of terrestrial biomarkers into the marine environment at the Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary, Caravaca, Spain",2005,"Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology","224","1-3",,"108","116",,,10.1016/j.palaeo.2005.03.032,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-23044480136&partnerID=40&md5=9394e95c7f19471097ed2b9aae531ba7","Department of Chemistry, Aichi Medical University, School of Medicine, Nagakute-cho, Aichi 480-1195, Japan; Department of Chemistry, Tokyo Metropolitan University, Tokyo 192-0364, Japan; Institute of Geology and Paleontology, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-8578, Japan; Departamento de Estratigrafía Y Paleontología, Universidad del País Vasco, Lejona 48940, Spain; Department of Legal Medicine, Aichi Medical University, School of Medicine, Nagakute-cho, Aichi 480-1195, Japan","Arinobu, T., Department of Chemistry, Aichi Medical University, School of Medicine, Nagakute-cho, Aichi 480-1195, Japan; Ishiwatari, R., Department of Chemistry, Tokyo Metropolitan University, Tokyo 192-0364, Japan; Kaiho, K., Institute of Geology and Paleontology, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-8578, Japan; Lamolda, M.A., Departamento de Estratigrafía Y Paleontología, Universidad del País Vasco, Lejona 48940, Spain; Seno, H., Department of Legal Medicine, Aichi Medical University, School of Medicine, Nagakute-cho, Aichi 480-1195, Japan","The mass extinction at the Cretaceous-Tertiary (K/T) boundary ca. 65 million years ago caused a major change in the nature and abundance of global life in Earth history. We present the first vertical high-resolution records of molecular distributions of n-fatty acids across the K/T boundary at Caravaca (Spain). The results reveal that the first basal thin horizon (0 to + 0.5 cm; 0 = K/T boundary) of the K/T boundary-clay layer showed as much as a ∼35-fold increase in concentrations of terrestrial long-chain n-fatty acids (≥ C 20), representative of an eight-fold increase in mass accumulation rate, compared with the subjacent Cretaceous layers. Thereafter concentrations rapidly declined back to almost pre-boundary values within + 3 cm above the K/T boundary. The abrupt increase in supply of terrestrial organic matter into the marine environment at the K/T boundary could have been caused by an enhanced riverine flux, probably due to heavy rains associated with global warming, combined with enhanced fragments of terrestrial higher-plants withered by acid rain and/or by temporal darkness and cooling. © 2005 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Biomarker; Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary; Fatty acid; Terrestrial influx","biomarker; Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary; fatty acid; sedimentation rate; terrigenous deposit; Eastern Hemisphere; Eurasia; Europe; Southern Europe; Spain; World; Embryophyta",,,,,,"Arinobu, T., Ishiwatari, R., Kaiho, K., Lamolda, M.A., Spike of pyrosynthetic polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons associated with an abrupt decrease in δ13C of a terrestrial biomarker at the Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary at Caravaca, Spain (1999) Geology, 27, pp. 723-726; Brooks, P.W., Eglinton, G., Gaskell, S.J., McHugh, D.J., Maxwell, J.R., Philip, R.P., Lipids of recent sediments: Part I. Straight-chain hydrocarbons and carboxylic acids of some temperate lacustrine and sub-tropical lagoonal tidal flat sediments (1976) Chemical Geology, 18, pp. 21-38; Canudo, J.I., Keller, G., Molina, E., Cretaceous/Tertiary boundary extinction pattern and faunal turnover at Agost and Caravaca, S.E. Spain (1991) Marine Micropaleontology, 17, pp. 319-341; Coccioni, R., Galeotti, S., K-T boundary extinction: Geologically instantaneous or gradual event? Evidence for deep-sea benthic foraminifera (1994) Geology, 22, pp. 779-782; Cranwell, P.A., Monocarboxylic acids in lake sediments: Indicators, derived from terrestrial and aquatic biota, of paleoenvironmental trophic levels (1974) Chemical Geology, 14, pp. 1-14; Fukushima, K., Ishiwatari, R., 